<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<%- include('../partials/head') %>
<body class="page page--<%= pageClass %>">
<%- include('../partials/header') %>
<main id="main" class="main">

  <section class="page-hero page-hero--compact">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow">Privacy</p>
      <h1 class="page-hero__title">Privacy policy</h1>
      <p class="page-hero__lead">Minimal collection, local-first products, and no surveillance-style growth tactics.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--legal">
    <div class="container narrow legal-stack">
      <article class="legal-card"><h2>Overview</h2><p>Faith Based Innovations, LLC builds desktop software intended to run primarily on your hardware. That posture shapes what we need from you online.</p></article>
      <article class="legal-card"><h2>What we collect</h2><p>We collect what is needed to operate the business: licensing, commerce, support, and security. We avoid collecting data “just in case.”</p></article>
      <article class="legal-card"><h2>What we do not do</h2><p>We do not build products around behavioral ad profiles. We do not sell attention as a product.</p></article>
      <article class="legal-card"><h2>Where data lives</h2><p>Application data is designed to remain on your device unless a feature explicitly uses an online service.</p></article>
      <article class="legal-card"><h2>Payments</h2><p>Payment processing uses specialized providers. When live, we will name them here.</p></article>
      <article class="legal-card"><h2>Your controls</h2><p>Local data can be removed by you directly. Account-related requests follow the process published with each product.</p></article>
      <article class="legal-card"><h2>Updates</h2><p>Material policy changes receive a visible effective date and a concise summary of what changed.</p></article>
    </div>
  </section>

</main>
<%- include('../partials/footer') %>
<%- include('../partials/mobile-nav') %>
<script type="module" src="/src/main.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
